description:
Für mich, weil ich sonst niemanden kenne, der ein richtiger Fan dieser Musik ist.

27.03. 1137 , 27.04. 1205 , 27.07. 1307 , 12.10. 1393
In March 2019 I started these playlist with 77 tracks in. The next 17 months I looked steadily for new alternative tracks with a real catchy melody to add until the limit of 500 songs in one playlist. This was reached in August 2020.  
[I have to admit that it's really hard to stick consequently to one genre that has such a wide range as the Alternative Rock has; however there are also a few crossovers from Indie, Ska, Blues, Rock, Psychobilly, Reggae, Punk, Country, Wave and Pop in between. standing for the wide range and I'm sure you'll like them too!]
By the way... from time to time it could be that  a song is replaced by a even more catchy one - and so done as said 7 month  after the list was completed I changed in 2021 at the 7th of January 177 songs and I think that's it, maybe ... ;) ... and exchanged 7x7 (49) songs at the beginning of March.

I hope the earworm songs will pocket you in the same way as they did and do to me!  :)

Rock on!
Stevo

description:
While my parents were playing 45s and LPs or R&B, soul, pop, disco, and salsa, I gravitated to a new sound...Rap. Friday nights, I'd stay up late listening to DJ Chuck Chillout and DJ Red Alert on KISS FM radio recording the shows on my double cassette tape boombox my father helped me purchase. 

Included is a collection of 90s Hip Hop collection that I danced to when I was old enough to start NYC clubbing in the 90s. 

This playlist is a work in progress, so add to your favorites to receive updates.
